    "created_at": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z",
    "notes": "GAP & GO BUYING STRATEGY. Logic: (1) Detects significant gap open (spot_change_pct > 0.5% up or < -0.5% down) in the first 42 minutes of session. (2) Only one leg enters \u2014 CE if gap up + PCR neutral/bearish, PE if gap down + PCR supports. (3) Buys ATM (0.50 delta) for maximum delta exposure during the gap run. (4) Two partial exits at 30% profit to lock in gains while keeping 50% position for further run. (5) HARD EXIT at 10:30 regardless of P&L \u2014 gaps either confirm or fill by then, holding beyond is speculation not strategy. (6) No entry on expiry day \u2014 gamma makes options unpredictable in the morning. (7) VIX < 20 gate \u2014 on high-VIX days gaps are noise, not signal. BEST DAYS: Budget day, RBI policy day, FII data day, geopolitical overnight news."
  },
